  <title>EVENT (Add and Remove)</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>ADD</keyword>
    <keyword>EVENT</keyword>
    <keyword>REMOVE</keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">EVENT (Add and Remove)</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal">XSharp now supports an extended Event syntax. Both a single line syntax is supported as a multi line:</para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">Old style syntax (compatible with Vulcan)</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example">[Attributes] [Modifiers] EVENT [&lt;ExplicitInterface&gt;.] &lt;Id&gt; AS &lt;Type&gt; &#160; &#160;// Old Style</para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">Single Line syntax with explicit expressions</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example">[Attributes] [Modifiers] EVENT [&lt;ExplicitInterface&gt;.] &lt;Id&gt; AS &lt;Type&gt; &#160; [ADD &lt;ExpressionList] [REMOVE &lt;ExpressionList] &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;// Single Line</para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">Multi line syntax with explicit expressions</para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example">[Attributes] [Modifiers] EVENT [&lt;ExplicitInterface&gt;.] &lt;Id&gt; AS &lt;Type&gt; &#160; &#160; // Multi line</para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example">ADD</para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"> &#160; &#160;&lt;Statements&gt;</para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example">END [ADD]</para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example">REMOVE</para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"> &#160; &#160;&lt;Statements&gt;</para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example">END [REMOVE]</para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example">END [EVENT]</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">Example </para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"><br/></para>
